{"article_id":"FwGHYcWhKZFpKuwf","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Yikes , we 're headed toward a fiscal cliff !","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"It will crush the economy !","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"Or so the media and politicians tell us .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The `` cliff '' is a series of tax increases and budget cuts","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that automatically go into effect Jan. 1","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"unless Congress acts .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"It will !","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"I see the future :","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"The politicians will meet","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"and fret","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"and hold press conferences","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"and predict disaster .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"Then they 'll reach a deal .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"It will just postpone the reckoning ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"but they 'll congratulate themselves ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"and the media will move on .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"`` They 're not going to admit","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that we 're bankrupt ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"and they wo n't admit","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that we 're on the verge of a major , major change in our society , ''","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"says Rep. Ron Paul , R-Texas .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"`` So they 'll keep putting it aside ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"but then we 'll eventually probably destroy the dollar . ''","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"The across-the-board cut , or `` sequestration , '' was designed to be so distasteful","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"that Congress would be moved to cut more deliberately .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"If it does n't act ,","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"$ 110 billion in projected spending will be automatically cut","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"-- half from domestic spending , half from the Pentagon .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"`` They assume","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"that they made it so bad","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"that they would n't accept it ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"but I do n't think","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"they did , ''","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"said Paul .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"`` They 're not even ... talking about real cuts .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"They 're talking about cuts in baseline budgeting . ''","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"`` If they propose ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"let 's say ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"a $ 10 billion increase for next year","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"and cut it down to $ 9 billion ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"they say","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"they 're cutting 10 percent .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"But they 're not cutting anything ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"they 're only increasing it $ 9 billion instead of $ 10 billion .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"It 's done on purpose","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"so that people get confused . ''","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Republican House Speaker John Boehner calls the fiscal cliff a `` nightmare .","depth":3},{"id":47,"text":"'' Cuts of $ 110 billion would even be good for us","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"because it would keep money in private hands , away from the bloated and freedom-killing bureaucracy .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"`` When government spending is about $ 3.8 trillion ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"you 're going to cut $ 100 billion ?","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"That 's a deck chair on the Titanic , ''","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"said Russ Roberts of the Hoover Institution .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"`` If they 're actual cuts ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"I think","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that would be great .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"I 'd cut 10 , 20 percent across the board","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"if I had my druthers .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"But across the board scares people","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"because they think ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"'Let 's save the things","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"that are really important","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"and cut the things","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"that are not so important . '","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"( But ) that never works .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"'' It does n't work","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"because every cent in the budget is absolutely crucial to someone .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Lately the media are focused on the $ 400 billion in tax increases","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"that make up four-fifths of the fiscal cliff .","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"We 're told that","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"if the Bush-era tax rate cuts expire","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"and the spending reductions kick in ,","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"catastrophe will follow .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"`` The tax increases sound scarier .","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"But we have a trillion dollar deficit ! ''","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"Roberts pointed out .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"`` So to me , the idea","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"of raising taxes","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"is probably a good idea .","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"It says","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"this spending","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"that we 've been doing","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"is not a free lunch . '' I 'm not convinced","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that giving politicians more money is ever a good idea .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"And wo n't the wealthy high-earners find a way around the higher rates ?","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"When rich people do that ,","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"much of their money goes to lawyers instead of consumer satisfaction .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"The other thing","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"that scares Washington","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"are the automatic cuts to Pentagon spending .","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"`` These draconian cuts represent a threat to our national security , ''","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"say Republican Sens . John McCain of Arizona and Lindsey Graham of South Carolina .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"`` The Pentagon is hysterical about it , ''","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"notes Ben Friedman of the Cato Institute .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"`` But it 's about 10 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"which would bring us roughly back to where we were in defense spending in 2006 ...","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"adjusted for inflation , not exactly a crisis year in the Pentagon .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"They 've gotten very spoiled at the Pentagon .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"They had years of luxury . ''","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"`` We need probably bigger cuts in the defense budget","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"because we do too much .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"This will force us to make some choices .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"We try to be everything in the world ...","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"pretending","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"that every unstable country is a threat to us . ''","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"I wo n't lose sleep over automatic spending cuts .","depth":4},{"id":106,"text":"The `` fiscal cliff '' frightens me less than the bankruptcy cliff .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":173,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":152,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":129,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":113,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":109,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":108,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":112,"left":111,"right":6,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":3,"right":110,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"p